 Books
Id: INT (Primary Key)

Title: NVARCHAR(MAX)

Year: INT

CoverUrl: NVARCHAR(MAX)

OpenLibraryId: NVARCHAR(MAX)

Authors
Id: INT (Primary Key)

Name: NVARCHAR(MAX)

Genres
Id: INT (Primary Key)

Name: NVARCHAR(MAX)

Moods
Id: INT (Primary Key)

Name: NVARCHAR(MAX)

Join Tables (Many-to-Many Relationships)
These tables are the key to your flexible schema, linking books to multiple authors, genres, and moods.

BookAuthors
BookId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Books.Id)

AuthorId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Authors.Id)

BookGenres
BookId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Books.Id)

GenreId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Genres.Id)

BookMoods
BookId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Books.Id)

MoodId: INT (PK, Foreign Key → Moods.Id)
